            <div class="w-full font-semibold prose print:font-normal lg:px-3 max-w-none"><p data-block-key="f0xar">It is recommended that the Royal College of Radiologists, working with the Society and College of Radiographers and other relevant specialties through the Academy of Royal Medical Colleges, develops:</p><ol><li data-block-key="rfauw">principles upon which findings should be reported as ‘unexpected significant’, ‘critical’ and ‘urgent’</li><li data-block-key="ckv93">a simplified national framework for the coding of alerts on radiology reports</li><li data-block-key="rl9ak">a list of conditions for which an alert should always be triggered, where appropriate and feasible to do so.</li></ol></div>
