                                        <div class="w-full prose lg:px-3 print:px-0 markdown max-w-none"><p data-block-key="91vrg">There is an established model of radiology departments requesting a CT scan for chest X-rays referred from GPs that show possible lung cancer. Two trusts are extending this to chest X-rays referred from the emergency department.</p><p data-block-key="c99dd">It would be beneficial for this practice to be evaluated.</p><p data-block-key="gje9q"><b>Observation to the Royal College of Radiologists:</b></p><p data-block-key="wyfod">Given the likely wider use of artificial intelligence in the future, some standardisation of radiology reports may be required. It would be beneficial for this to be evaluated.</p></div>
